description:
The getFreePort function has a time-of-check-time-of-use race condition:

func getFreePort() (int, error) {
    l, err := net.Listen(tcp, 127.0.0.1:0)
    if err != nil {
        return 0, err
    }
    defer l.Close()  // Port is released here
    return l.Addr().(*net.TCPAddr).Port, nil
}

Between closing the listener and the actual Dolt server starting, another process could claim that port.

Impact: Flaky tests when ports collide. Could cause test failures that are hard to reproduce.

Fix: Use OS-assigned ports that remain bound, or implement a port reservation system.

The getPrefixFromGT function errors are silently ignored:

prefix, err := getPrefixFromGT(ctx, runner, plan.Name.ValueString())
if err == nil {
    plan.Prefix = types.StringValue(prefix)
}
// If err != nil, no diagnostic, no warning - prefix just stays empty

This happens in both Create and Read operations for the rig resource.

Impact: Users see empty prefix attribute with no indication why. Makes debugging difficult.

Fix: Add a warning diagnostic when prefix cannot be retrieved, or document that prefix may be empty.
